<C>__{salesman}
<D>__{you can't expect me to pay you for your attachment to that car.}
<A>__{landon gazes at another dealership across the street, then adopts the surly, vaguely threatening attitude of old.}
<C>__{landon}
<D>__{i don't. i expect you to pay me for yours.}
<A>__{the salesman looks from landon to the car. he pulls a wad of cash from his pocket. wearily counts out twelve bills. landon takes the money, touches the camaro's hood, then walks away.}
